  <h1>
   font_get_size
  </h1>
  With this function you can get the size of any font resource, which is the point value shown by the font resource dialogue.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">font_get_size(ind);
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      ind
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../The_Asset_Editors/Fonts.htm">
        Font Asset
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      Index of the font to get the size of.
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 Real
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">sz = font_get_size(font0);
</code></pre>
  This will get the size of the font indexed by the "font0" variable and store it in the variable "sz".
 </body>
</html>